body:
# Pull Request Management

Pull requests are the primary collaboration mechanism on GitHub. They propose changes from a head branch (or fork) into a base branch, enable code review, run CI checks via [[github/actions]], and provide a merge gate for protected branches.

## Creating a Pull Request

```javascript
import { Octokit } from "@octokit/rest";

const octokit = new Octokit({ auth: process.env.GITHUB_TOKEN });

const { data: pr } = await octokit.pulls.create({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  title: "feat: add user authentication",
  body: "## Summary\nAdds JWT-based authentication.\n\nFixes #42\n\n## Test Plan\n- [x] Unit tests pass\n- [x] Integration tests pass",
  head: "feature/auth",
  base: "main",
  draft: false,
});
console.log(pr.number, pr.html_url, pr.mergeable);
```

## Requesting Reviews

```javascript
await octokit.pulls.requestReviewers({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  pull_number: pr.number,
  reviewers: ["reviewer-1", "reviewer-2"],
  team_reviewers: ["security-team"],
});
```

## Submitting a Review

```javascript
await octokit.pulls.createReview({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  pull_number: pr.number,
  event: "APPROVE",  // APPROVE, REQUEST_CHANGES, or COMMENT
  body: "LGTM! Code looks clean and tests are comprehensive.",
});
```

## Checking Status

```javascript
// Get combined status (CI checks)
const { data: status } = await octokit.repos.getCombinedStatusForRef({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  ref: "feature/auth",
});
console.log(status.state); // success, failure, pending

// Get check runs (GitHub Actions)
const { data: checks } = await octokit.checks.listForRef({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  ref: "feature/auth",
});
```

## Merging

```javascript
// Merge with a specific strategy
await octokit.pulls.merge({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  pull_number: pr.number,
  merge_method: "squash",  // merge, squash, or rebase
  commit_title: "feat: add user authentication (#42)",
  commit_message: "Adds JWT-based auth with refresh tokens.",
});
```

## Merge Strategies

| Strategy | Command | Result |
|----------|---------|--------|
| Merge commit | `merge_method: "merge"` | Preserves all commits, adds merge commit |
| Squash | `merge_method: "squash"` | Combines into single commit |
| Rebase | `merge_method: "rebase"` | Replays commits on base, linear history |

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|----------|
| `GITHUB_TOKEN` | Personal access token or installation token |
